76.4	Extensible_Application_Markup_Language	Extensible Application Markup Language	Extensible Application Markup Language (XAML, ) is a declarative XML-based language created by Microsoft used for initializing structured values and objects. It is available under Microsoft's Open Specification Promise. The acronym originally stood for Extensible Avalon Markup Language - Avalon being the code-name for Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF).	
